⁶ i.e., as a sign of secrecy. After Domitim something like narrat must be supplied. This Domitius is Lucius Domitius Ahenobarbus, who married Porcia, sister of M. Cato. He was a faithful supportet of the aristocratical party. He was aedile in 61, praetor in 58, and consul in 54. When the Civil War broke out in 49 he threw himself into Corfinium, but his own troops forced him to surrender- to Caesar. He then went to Massilia, and on the sui-render of that town, joined Pompey in Greece. He commanded the lest wing in the battle of Pharsalia, in which he fell (according to Cicero) by the hand of Antony.
